      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">6</infon>
        <offset>757</offset>
        <text>The viral shunt, releasing on a global scale ~0.37-0.63 gigatonnes of carbon per year, is an essential source of labile organic detritus in the deep-sea ecosystems.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">7</infon>
        <offset>922</offset>
        <text>This process sustains a high prokaryotic biomass and provides an important contribution to prokaryotic metabolism, allowing the system to cope with the severe organic resource limitation of deep-sea ecosystems.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">8</infon>
        <offset>1133</offset>
        <text>Our results indicate that viruses have an important role in global biogeochemical cycles, in deep-sea metabolism and the overall functioning of the largest ecosystem of our biosphere.
</text>
      </sentence>
